wöhnlichen organisatorischen Hintergründe zu rekonstruieren und argumentative Schwachstellen des kuratorischen Konzepts zu beleuchten. So wird schließlich am Beispiel der sieben ausgestellten Architekten eine Annäherung an einen fundierte(re)n Begriff von der dekonstruktivistischen Architektur ermöglicht.  a»Deconstructivist Architecture« - a success story? The background to an exhibition that was as controversial as it was successful, and which wrote architectural history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArchitecture and DesignxArchitecture and Design, other. 4aBernard Tschumi. 4aCoop Himmelb(l)au. 4aDaniel Libeskind. 4aDeconstructivist Architecture. 4aDekonstruktion. 4aFrank Gehry. 4aMuseum of Modern Art. 4aMuseum. 4aMuseumswissenschaft. 4aNew York. 4aPeter Eisenman. 4aPhilip Johnson. 4aRem Koolhaas. 4aZaha Hadid. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aBernard Tschumi.  aCoop Himmelb(l)au.  aDaniel Libeskind.  aDeconstruction.  aDeconstructivist Architecture.  aFrank Gehry.  aMuseology.  aMuseum of Modern Art.  aMuseum.  aNew York.  aPeter Eisenman.  aPhilip Johnson.  aRem Koolhaas.  aZaha Hadid.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839430293zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/978383943